CUCUMBER HOOKS -- technical stake holders

BACKGROUND -- SHOULD BE PART OF FEATURE FILE

NOT PART OF FEATURE FILE
CAN BE WRITTEN IN STEP DEFINITION CLASS
OR CAN BE WRITTEN IN A SEPARATE CONFIGURATION CLASS


setup and tear down

@Before -- will be executed before each scenario
@After -- will be executed after each scenario


@BeforeStep -- before each step of the scenario
@AfterStep -- after each step of the scenario


Annotate tags with hooks:

@Smoke
scenario search

@Smoke
scenario advanced search

@Regression
scenario home page feature

===================================================================================

Given: Preconditions are mentioned in the Given keyword. The Steps of the 
Given keyword put the system in to a know state, which is necessary for the 
user action. Avoid talking about user interaction in Given Steps.

When: The purpose of the When Steps is to describe the user action.

Then: The purpose of Then Steps is to observe the expected output. The
observations should be related to the business value/ benefit of your Feature description.


	And: This is used for statements that are an addition to the previous
	Steps and represent positives statements.
	
	But: This is used for statements that are an addition to previous Steps
	and represent negative statements.
	
	In a Step Definitions file, And and But are listed as Given/When/Then, the
	keyword that they appear after. There are no And and But keywords in
	Step Definitions.   






















